HEADWORD: Parvolin
<hw>Par"vo*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A nonoxygenous ptomaine, formed in the putrefaction of
albuminous matters, especially of horseflesh and mackerel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

